					<h3>Norwich Sound & Vision</h3>
					<p>
						Saturday 10th October 2015 is ladies day at NS&V, there'll be plenty of great female acts gracing the stages all over the city, but at The Plasterers Arms we'll be bringing you live music and then DJs into the early hours of the morning.
						And of course we'll be the only venue with loads of brewster brewed beers!
					</p>
					<h3>The Fat Plasterers London Festival</h3>
					<p>
						Saturday 14th November 2015 <br>
						The Plasterers Arms are teaming up with the only other pub worth its salt in the North City for a weekend of music and beer, all brought up from the big smoke.
						There'll be music every day over the weekend at both venues, but Fem.Ale are proud to organising Saturday's festivities, and we'll be bringing you music from Hattie Marsh and beer from some of London's best brewsters.  
						We'll also be hosting a meet the brewer with some of the girls behind Beavertown brewery.
					</p>
